Introduction
************

The UMS project is based on the team work of many individual
programmers.  This has led to some chaos regarding file names,
directories and archives. This text contains of guidelines for all who
want to release a package for the UMS project. The ultimate goal should
be that the complete UMS project gets an uniform structure. The users
will hopefully be grateful :-)


@EndNode

@Node "Directory Structure" "filenameguide.guide/Directory Structure"
@Next "File Names"
@Prev "Introduction"
@Toc "Main"

Directory Structure
*******************

All applications, which are related to the UMS project, are joined in
one directory with the name @{b}UMS@{ub}. Due to the uniform structure every
file gets its unique location. The names of the subdirectories should
@{i}not@{ui} contain the name @{b}UMS@{ub} anymore.

   Directory @{b}UMS/@{ub}:

@{b}UMS/Bin/@{ub}
     UMS programs und AmigaDOS script files

@{b}UMS/Developer/@{ub}
     Informations for programmers

@{b}UMS/Devs/@{ub}
     Devices

@{b}UMS/Doc/@{ub}
     Documentation for UMS programs

@{b}UMS/Install/@{ub}
     Script files for Installer

@{b}UMS/L/@{ub}
     All files, which belong into L:

@{b}UMS/Libs/@{ub}
     Libraries

@{b}UMS/Locale/@{ub}
     Catalogs, same directory structure as in LOCALE:

@{b}UMS/Networks/@{ub}
     Network specific Im-/Exporters

@{b}UMS/Reader/@{ub}
     Message reader

@{b}UMS/Rexx/@{ub}
     UMS ARexx script files

@{b}UMS/S/@{ub}
     Additions for S:User-Startup

@{b}UMS/Tools/@{ub}
     All programs which do not belong to Networks/Reader


@EndNode

